-- Unicredit soon to let suitors look at debt collection unit data
-- 
-- Mon May 05, 2014 06:36AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 5 (Reuters) - Italy's Unicredit <CRDI.MI> will soon let potential buyers of its Credit Management Bank unit look at its financial data, the lender's Chief Executive Federico Ghizzoni said on Monday.

"We are about to open the data room (to interested parties)," Ghizzoni told reporters on the sidelines of an event.